OL,3,CNo evidence of 'two-tier policing' in
OL,4,Csummer riots response, MPs say
OL,6,FIt found there was no evidence of "two-
OL,7,Ftier policing" in officers' handling
OL,8,Fof the levels of violence and
OL,9,Fcriminality during the period, and
OL,10,Fbranded the claims as "disgraceful".
OL,12,FMPs said: "This was not protest. Those
OL,13,Fparticipating in disorder were not
OL,14,Fpoliced more strongly because of their
OL,15,Fsupposed political views but because
OL,16,Fthey were throwing missiles,
OL,17,Fassaulting police officers and
OL,18,Fcommitting arson.
